		<div>The cycle is always the same:<br />
- when an expansion is new, clerics are greatly in demand for healing and res<br />
- as an expansion ages and tanks gain 2k+hp, cleric importance greatly wanes<br />
<br />
When PoP came out it was a shock how hard mobs hit. I suspect noone ever thought we'd get to the point a (good) druid could be main healer in PoFire.<br />
Ditto with LDoN hards once tanks and support classes aug'd up.<br />
<br />
GoD will go that way too, mark my words.<br />
<br />
Healing (and res) is pretty much all clerics have. If you remove that from them (by sharing it around too much) you have to improve their dps or utility someway else. Yeah clerics will always be in demand for raids but it's both a stressful and boring job. Some clerics love being 'needed' for raids but I think most just do it out of duty (and to get the loot).</div>
