		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I just PL'ed the hell out of my cleric for exactly this reason.  Very well said.<br />
<br />
It's a source of confusion why we accept near parity for ourselves (versus mages, necros, rogues) in our primary skill while we rail against parity for clerics (versus druids, shamans) in theirs.  If we accept mages, necros and rogues as our partners in high DPS, why should clerics not have partners in healing?<br />
<br />
It'd be a pleasant change to see people say &quot;mages, necros and rogues should be 65-70% of a wizard in DPS.&quot; Personally, I think parity is a pain in my white Irish ass, and is designed to make the game easier to play solo...a tend the dev team tries to reverse, half-heartedly and only when a full moon is out.  Clerics are *supposed* to be masters at healing, the same as we're *supposed* to be masters at spellcasting.  That's why the less pure classes have pets, lich, sneak, dot, heal, all the stuff we don't.<br />
<br />
But that ship sailed long ago, and I don't like that we left clerics behind.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
